---
const pageTitle = "Cyber Robbery";
---

<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <title>{pageTitle}</title>
  </head>
      <body>
                <header class="project-hero">
                  <h1>{pageTitle}</h1>
                  <div class="project-meta">
                    <span><strong>Type:</strong> Video Game/App</span>
                    <span><strong>Timeline:</strong> 1 Week</span>
                    <span><strong>Purpose:</strong> Congressional App Challenge</span>
                  </div>
                </header>

                <section class="description-box">
                    <p>
                    Cyber Robbery was an App that works like an interactive clicker video game created to educate
                    players on cyber security topics such as secure passwords, phishing and malware.
                    It was made for the annual Congressional App Challenge where students from around the
                    country compete to make an app to be displayed on the website of the White House. The app
                    was coded in JavaScript with a teammate. This project taught me how make learning interactive,
                    make a common structure for code with a teammate, and to manage large boolean expressions.
                    </p>
                </section>

                <figure class="screenshot-card">
                    <img src="/cyberRobbery/characterSelectionCR.png" alt="Character Selection" />
                        <figcaption>
                        Character selection and a tutorial offered in the menu.
                        </figcaption>
                </figure>

                <figure class="screenshot-card">
                    <img src="/cyberRobbery/storyCR.png" alt="Story" />
                        <figcaption>
                        The story starts with the players money being taken.
                        They will then have to travel to different locations finding
                        clues to the whereabouts of their money while learning cyber
                         security topics. The gameplay loop consists of entering a location,
                          clicking different clues and finding where one of three bosses
                          are, and having their knowledge tested in form of a boss fight.
                           Once a boss is defeated they lead the player to the next place.
                           </figcaption>
                </figure>

                <figure class="screenshot-card">
                    <img src="/cyberRobbery/mapCR.png" alt="Map" />
                        <figcaption>
                        The map's different locations appear as the player
                        progresses.
                        </figcaption>
                </figure>

                <figure class="screenshot-card">
                    <img src="/cyberRobbery/roomsCR.png" alt="Rooms" />
                        <figcaption>
                        2 examples of rooms the player will encounter.
                        </figcaption>
                </figure>

                <figure class="screenshot-card">
                    <img src="/cyberRobbery/cluesCR.png" alt="Clues" />
                        <figcaption>
                        These are some examples of clues the player may find.
                        </figcaption>
                </figure>

                <figure class="screenshot-card">
                    <img src="/cyberRobbery/questionsCR.png" alt="Questions" />
                        <figcaption>
                        These are examples of questions that may be
                        asked during boss fights. The answers to many are found in clues.
                        </figcaption>
                </figure>

                <figure class="screenshot-card">
                    <img src="/cyberRobbery/codeCR.png" alt="Code" />
                        <figcaption>
                        Code Showcase.
                        </figcaption>
                </figure>

                    <footer class="bottom-nav">
                        <a href="/" class="home-button">Home</a>
                    </footer>
      </body>
</html>

<style>
.project-hero {
    background-color: #2DD4BF;
    border: 4px solid #0EA5E9;
    border-radius: 16px;
    padding: 40px 20px;
    margin-bottom: 40px;
    text-align: center;
    box-shadow: 0 0 20px rgba(34, 197, 94, 0.2);
  }

.project-hero h1 {
    color: #ffffff;
    font-size: 3rem;
    margin: 0;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 2px;
    text-shadow: 2px 2px 4px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.5);
  }

.project-meta {
    margin-top: 15px;
    display: flex;
    justify-content: center;
    gap: 20px;
    color: #ffffff;
    font-size: 1.1rem;
  }

.project-meta span {
    background: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.3);
    padding: 5px 15px;
    border-radius: 20px;
  }

.description-box {
    background-color: #262626;
    border: 4px solid #3f3f46;
    border-radius: 12px;
    padding: 25px;
    margin-bottom: 40px;
    line-height: 1.6;
    color: #d1d5db;
  }

.description-box p {
    margin-bottom: 15px;
  }

body {
    max-width: 800px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 20px;
    font-family: arial;
    background-color: #1a1a1a;
    color: #f3f4f6;
  }

.screenshot-card {
    background-color: #2d2d2d;
    border-radius: 12px;
    padding: 16px;
    margin-bottom: 40px;
    box-shadow: 0 8px 16px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.4);
    text-align: center;
  }

.screenshot-card img {
    max-width: 100%;
    border-radius: 8px;
    height: auto;
  }

.screenshot-card figcaption {
    margin-top: 15px;
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    color: #2DD4BF;
  }

.multi-image-card {
    background-color: #2d2d2d;
    border-radius: 12px;
    padding: 16px;
    margin-bottom: 40px;
    box-shadow: 0 8px 16px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.4);
  }

.image-group {
    display: flex;
    gap: 10px;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    justify-content: center;
  }

.image-group img {
    flex: 1;
    min-width: 300px;
    max-width: 48%;
    height: auto;
    border-radius: 8px;
  }

figcaption {
    margin-top: 15px;
    text-align: center;
    color: #2DD4BF;
    font-style: italic;
  }

.bottom-nav {
    margin-top: 60px;
    padding: 40px 0;
    border-top: 1px solid #374151;
    display: flex;
    justify-content: center;
  }

a {
    color: #2DD4BF;
    text-decoration: none;
    font-weight: bold;
  }

.home-button {
    display: inline-block;
    background-color: #0EA5E9;
    color: white;
    padding: 16px 32px;
    font-size: 1.2rem;
    font-weight: bold;
    text-decoration: none;
    border-radius: 50px;
    transition: all 0.3s ease;
    box-shadow: 0 4px 15px rgba(14, 165, 233, 0.4);
  }

.home-button:hover {
    background-color: #0EA5E9;
    transform: translateY(-3px);
    box-shadow: 0 6px 20px rgba(14, 165, 233, 0.6);
  }
</style>